record.text: Check your own engagement level here. You'll need to follow lots more people and build up a following. It takes time. There is no algorithm that boosts posts here. It's also possible, however, that your posting style finds a more receptive audience on the Xitter than here. So be it.
It's the "probably" that I'm taking issue with.
You are following 124 accounts. I follow more than 4,000 and am seeing not an echo chamber but a place where people often disagree with each other, sometimes quite vehemently.
I'm glad you are posting here, but I also understand why Twitter might be a better fit for your style. Sort of like fish that prefer to swim in muddy water. 😂

Come to think of it, Google Plus was pretty good as a forum venue. I have continued to connect with many of the participants I met there, as they move from one platform to the next; but G+ was the greatest thing since Usenet.

One thing I miss when using Twitter and now Bluesky or Mastodon is the Usenet forums focus on specific topics. I follow many whisky people but our posts get mixed into the general stream. We can individually create lists or feeds, but it's not the same experience.

Those discussion forums, though, were great because there were so many of them with so many different topics. I used to troll a Japanese smoking group, as an anti-smoker, but it was all good fun and I even got invited to an off-kai (which they made non-smoking).
